The paper deals with fault tolerance and recovery techniques in data structures, which are typically studied in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses dynamic allocation and pointer organization, which are relevant to Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
